<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
          xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuMove">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Move</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: Move a block in the active editor Scicos window</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This menu may be used to move a set of<link
      linkend="XcosSelect">selected</link> objects. Once the menu as
      been activated the selected objects follow the mouse
      displacement til the user presses the left mouse button to give
      the final position or the right one to cancel the move.
    </para>
    <para>
      Note that during the move the links connected to two selected
      blocks follow the block displacement even if there are not
      selected.
    </para>
    <para>
      It is also possible to move a simple block or link just pressing
      the mouse over it (with the left button) and draging the block
      up to the desired position. Releasing the mouse button then
      finishes the move.  </para>
      <para> 
	Right click cancel the move action.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuCopy">Copy</link> </member>
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuDelete">Delete</link> </member>
    </simplelist>
   </refsection>
</refentry>
